10. g4 h6 11. f4 Nbd7 {, and now} 12. g5 $6 hxg5 13. fxg5 d5 $1 14. Bf4 Bd6 $36
{leaves White's king very exposed.}) 10... Nbd7 11. a4 ({Another redaction of
the same idea is} 11. Bg5 $5 Be7 12. a4 bxa4 (12... b4 $6 13. Nd5 exd5 14. exd5
{is more dangerous for Black.}) 13. Nd5 ({After} 13. Rxa4 O-O 14. Nb3 Nb6 {
Black's knight reaches c4 and puts a strong pressure on White's queenside.}) 13...
exd5 14. exd5 {This was successfully tried twice by GM Leniart. Here I can
suggest an improvement over Black's play:} h6 $5 $146 15. Bxf6 gxf6 16. Nf5 Ne5
{Letting White to regain the piece. On the other hand, it significantly
improves the pawn sctructure.} 17. Nxe7 Kxe7 18. f4 Bc8 {The Bb7 already did
its job.} 19. fxe5 fxe5 20. Rxa4 Bd7 {The Ke7 feels safe in the centre, so
Black should be OK.}) 11... b4 12. Na2 ({The more aggressive} 12. Nd5 exd5 13.
exd5+ {is well met by} Ne5 $1 (13... Kd8 $2 14. Nc6+ Bxc6 15. dxc6 $18 {
Quintiliano Pinto,R - De Oliveira,A Cuiaba 2021}) 14. f4 O-O-O $1 15. fxe5 dxe5
{Black takes over the initiative.}) 12... Nc5 13. Nxb4 ({Possible is also} 13.
c3 b3 14. Nxb3 Ncxe4 $132) 13... Ncxe4 14. Bf4 {This position occured in
Danielyan,V - Pantsulaia,L Tbilisi 2017} {Inmy opinion, White's last move
should be naturally met by} e5 15. Qd3 Nc5 16. Qf5 Bxg2 17. Kxg2 Be7 $132 {
Black is close for completing development, when his pawn structure is superior.
}) 8... b4 9. Na4 {The Na4 is misplaced, but it can be defended easily with
b2-b3.} ({Too passive is} 9. Nb1 $6 Nc6 10. Be3 Qc7 $15 {Aleksic,N - Razuvaev,
Y Cutro 2000}) 9... Qa5 10. b3 Nc6 11. Bb2 ({has no independent value, as
Black cat at least play} 11. Be3 Nxd4 {with a transposition.} (11... Rc8 $5)
12. Bxd4) 11... Nxd4 12. Bxd4 {White is leading in the development, so Black
should be very accurate form now.} e5 $1 {It is a good moment for fixing the
pawn structure and eliminating the possibility of ..e4-e5.} 13. Bb6 ({After} 
13. Be3 Nxe4 14. Nb6 {the activity of pieces offers White a definite
compensation for the central pawn, but hardly it suffices for more than
