Nc3 {In most cases, this move might lead to positions from the other Chapters.
However, there are few independent cases.} Nc6 {Worth attention is} 8. f4 $5 {
For some reason, this natural move is practically unexplored.} (8. Qg4 Nf6 9.
Qg3 {transposes to 7.Qg4}) (8. Bf4 {This move looks challenging for Black: the
desertion of Black's bishop of a3-f8 diagonal makes d6 vulnerable.} e5 $1 {
This somewhat weakening move is justified by the poor location of White's
bishop.} ({The more common} 8... d6 9. Qd2 Nge7 {is hardly sufficient for
equality in view of} 10. O-O-O e5 11. Be3 Bxe3 12. Qxe3 O-O 13. f4 $14) 9. Bg3
h5 $1 $146 {Black continued to play energetically. This move is a novelty.} 10.
h3 ({After} 10. h4 Nf6 11. Qd2 O-O 12. O-O-O d6 {the inclusion of h2-h4 and
h7-h5 makes the residence of Black's king safe.}) 10... h4 11. Bh2 Qg5 $1 {
After gaining space on the kingside Black feels free to activate his queen.}
12. O-O Rh6 13. Nd5 ({The endgame, that arises after} 13. Qd2 Qxd2 14. Nxd2 d6
15. Nd5 Rb8 {is acceptable for Black due to his strong dark-squared bishop.})
13... Rg6 14. Qf3 d6 $1 {The activity of heavy pieces offers Black an
excellent counterplay. The following line is illustrative:} 15. Nc7+ $6 Kf8 16.
Nxa8 $2 {This is consistent but bad...} Rf6 17. Qe2 Bxh3 {with a checkmate.}) (
8. Qe2 d6 9. Be3 b5 $1 {transposes to 7.Qe2}) 8... d5 $146 {In my opinion,
this energetic response is the best way to claim the drawbacks of early f2-f4.}
(8... d6 {is what was mostly tried in practice but after} 9. Qf3 Nf6 10. Be3
Bxe3 11. Qxe3 O-O 12. O-O-O {, followed by g2-g4 White's attacking chances
seem preferable.}) 9. Qf3 ({The other possibilities are:} 9. Qg4 Nf6 $1 10.
Qxg7 Rg8 11. Qh6 dxe4 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Qb6 $44 {The strong Ba7 puts
White's king is in danger. Black has full compensation for a pawn.}) ({White
achieves no advantage also with} 9. exd5 exd5 10. Qe2+ Nge7 11. Bd2 O-O 12.
O-O-O Re8 {The active piece play fully compensates for the isolated d5-pawn.})
9... Nb4 $1 10. Bd2 Nxd3+ 11. cxd3 Ne7 12. O-O-O O-O {Black is doing perfectly
fine.} *

