36,22,22,10,13,7,13,-18,-8,-8,3]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5.
Bd3 Bc5 6. Nb3 Ba7 7. O-O Nc6 8. Nc3 Nf6 9. Qe2 {As after 7.Qe2 White's main
idea is exchanging the dark-squared bishops.} (9. Kh1 d6 10. f4 ({Dubious is} 
10. Bg5 $6 h6 11. Bh4 g5 12. Bg3 h5 13. Be2 e5 {The bad Bg3 allowed Black to
take over the initiative in Pogonina,N - Christiansen,L Kapuskasing 2003})
10... h5 $5 {An interesting concept: Black leaves the king in the centre, but
