retreat diminishes White's control of d5 and after} d5 16. e5 Ne4 {Black
obtains an excellent position, where both his bishops are very effective.})
10... Bxe3 {I see nothing wrong with an immediate exchange.} (10... b5 $5 {
was also successfully tried on the high level.}) 11. Qxe3 O-O 12. Rad1 ({
The straightforward} 12. f4 e5 13. f5 Ne7 {offers Black a comfortable play
because of the potential d6-d5 break. For instance,} 14. a4 Bd7 15. Be2 Rc8 $15 {
Georgiadis, N - Milov, V Switzerland 2014}) 12... Qc7 {A decent move: Black
avoids the nasty opposition along the d-file and also takes more control of e5}
13. Kh1 ({Premature is} 13. f4 $2 Ng4 14. Qh3 Qb6+ 15. Kh1 Ne3 16. e5 h6 $17)
13... b5 14. f4 Bb7 {Now, when f2-f4 is played fianchetto becomes a very
attractive option.} 15. Qh3 b4 16. Ne2 Rfd8 {Black didn't have any problems in
