with} 10. Kh1 {doesn't change much:} Ne5 11. f4 Nxd3 12. cxd3 O-O 13. Bd2 (13.
Nc3 b5 {transposes to 10.Nc3}) 13... b5 14. Nc3 {We have been following
Sakelsek, T - Muzychuk, A Murska Sobota 2007} {Once again, Black should have
attacked the Nc3:} b4 15. Ne2 a5 16. Nbd4 Bd7 {The bishops pair fully
compensates for White's space advantage.}) 10... b5 11. Kh1 ({After} 11. Qxg7
Rg8 12. Qh6 Ne5 13. Qh3 Bb7 14. Be3 b4 {Black managed to quickly regain the
