e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Bd3 Bc5 6. Nb3 Ba7 (6... Be7 {is somewhat more
common, but I like leaving the bishop on the most attractive diagonal.}) 7. Qe2
{By making this move White illustrates, that he is interested in exchanging
the dark-squared bishops.} Nc6 8. Be3 (8. Nc3 {is mostly connected with an
intention to play ..0-0-0} d6 9. Be3 b5 10. Bxa7 ({The same reaction should
