e5 13. f5 b5 14. N1d2 Re7 15. Kh1 Bb7 {Black reached a harmonious setup and
might even consider the ambitious ...d6-d5. Ganguly,S - Mahjoob,M Esfahan 2005}
) 12... b5 13. Kh1 ({Premature is} 13. e5 $2 dxe5 14. fxe5 Qb6+ 15. Kh1 Nd7 $17
{,and the pawn is gone.}) 13... e5 {This standard consolidating move makes
Black's king safer.} (13... Nb4 $5 14. e5 dxe5 15. fxe5 Nd7 {also offers Black
an acceptable play}) 14. a4 bxa4 15. Rxa4 exf4 16. Rxf4 {This was Akopian,V -
Mamedov,N Antalya 2013 At this point I mostly like:} Ne5 17. Bxa6 {This is the
only way to fight for an advantage.} Be6 18. Bb5 Rxa4 19. Nxa4 Bxb3 20. cxb3
Qa5 {Black has an excellent compensation for a pawn due to strong Ne5.} *

