after all, there are also some downsides behind b2-b4.} ({The preceding game
saw} 9... Ne7 10. Bb2 Ng6 11. g3 Qc7 12. Qh5 $14 {White was better in Lomasov,
S - Rublevsky, S Struga 2021}) 10. Rb1 ({Harmless is} 10. bxa5 Qxa5 11. O-O Nf6
12. Qe2 Be7 {the damaged pawn structure offers Black a decent counterplay.})
10... axb4 11. axb4 Ra4 $1 {A decent move: it is provoking White to play ..
c2-c3, and it makes fianchetto irrelevant.} 12. c3 Qb8 {Black covers b5 and
the diagonal b8-h2.} 13. O-O (13. Qe2 {is also well met by} Bd6 14. Nf3 Nf6 15.
Nd4 Be5 {Black has no problems.}) 13... Bd6 14. Nf3 Nf6 15. Re1 Ng4 $1 {
The control of e5 is extremely important.} 16. h3 Ne5 $11 *

